configuration.name: preprocessScript
initScript
configuration.value:
/*
 * Available objects:
 *   sdc.state: A Map<String, Object> that is preserved between invocations of this script.
 *          Useful for caching bits of data, e.g. counters.
 *   sdc.log.<level>(msg, obj...): Use instead of println to send log messages to the log4j log
 *                             instead of stdout.
 *                             loglevel is any log4j level: e.g. info, warn, error, trace.
 *   sdc.getFieldNull(Record, 'field path'): Receive a constant defined above
 *                          to check if the field is typed field with value null
 *   sdc.createMap(boolean listMap): Create a map for use as a field in a record.
 *                          Pass true to this function to create a list map (ordered map)
 *   sdc.createEvent(String type, int version): Creates a new event.
 *                          Create new empty event with standard headers.
 *   sdc.toEvent(Record): Send event to event stream
 *                          Only events created with sdc.createEvent are supported.
 *   sdc.pipelineParameters(): Map with pipeline runtime parameters.
 */

// sdc.state['connection'] = new Connection().open();

import com.jcraft.jsch.*
import groovy.util.*

config = new java.util.Properties()
config.put "StrictHostKeyChecking", "no"

pipeline_params = sdc.pipelineParameters()
sftp_user = pipeline_params.get("SFTP_USER")
sftp_pass = pipeline_params.get("SFTP_PASS")
sftp_server = pipeline_params.get("SFTP_SERVER")
sftp_port = java.lang.Integer.parseInt(pipeline_params.get("SFTP_PORT"))
xsd_filename = pipeline_params.get("XSD_FILENAME")
local_xsd_filename = pipeline_params.get("LOCAL_XSD_FILENAME")
type_to_parse = pipeline_params.get("TYPE_TO_PARSE")

ssh = new JSch()
sess = ssh.getSession sftp_user, sftp_server, sftp_port

ssh = new JSch()
sess = ssh.getSession sftp_user, sftp_server, sftp_port
sess.setConfig config
sess.setPassword sftp_pass
sess.connect()
sftp_string = new java.lang.String("sftp")
chan = sess.openChannel sftp_string
chan.connect()

sftp = (ChannelSftp) chan
input_stream = sftp.get xsd_filename
new File(local_xsd_filename).append(input_stream)
input_stream.close()
chan.exit()
sess.disconnect()

xsd_doc = new XmlParser().parse(local_xsd_filename)
record_field_names = []
complex_type_element = xsd_doc.findAll { it.@name == type_to_parse }
complex_type_element[0].children()[0].each {
  record_field_names.add(it.@name + ".0.value")
}

sdc.state["record_field_names"] = record_field_names

sdc.log.info("record field names: " + record_field_names)

new File(local_xsd_filename).delete()

configuration.name: script
destroyScript

configDefinitions.name: conf.remoteConfig.ftpsMode
configDefinitions.description: Sets the FTPS encryption negotiation mode to either "Explicit" (also called FTPES) or "Implicit". "Implicit" assumes that encryption will be used immediately, while "Explicit" means that plain FTP will be used to connect and then encryption will be negotiated.
configDefinitions.label: FTPS Mode

configDefinitions.name: conf.remoteConfig.ftpsDataChannelProtectionLevel
configDefinitions.description: Sets the FTPS data channel protection level to either "Clear" (equivalent of "PROT C") or "Private" (equivalent of "PROT P").  "Private" means that the communication and data are both encrypted, while "Clear" means that only the communication is encrypted.
configDefinitions.label: FTPS Data Channel Protection Level
